left class=m><span class=title> Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> Just wanted to ask if a 25% hit ratio on Lure of Frost is normal for large mobs.  <br>
<br>
I have been in fear a total of 10 times.  Twice, the Golumns where up and my lure hit at a 25% ratio.<br>
<br>
In tackling 2nd Floor mobs and Spite Golums in hate, I counted again a 25% hit ratio.<br>
<br>
There was one other place, cannot rememeber.  But my guild leader smiled at me after we had slain a mob.  When I told her I was not the cause of the creatures death becuase I had hit 2 out of 6 lures, she dropped her Jaw.<br>
<br>
I am level 54.  Is it my level?  Is the Lure line always resisted this much?<br>
<br>
Lorielaen Shadu'Fay<br>
54th lvl Wizard<br>
Terris Thule<br>
 <p>Lorielaen Shadu'Fay
52nd Level Channelor
Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ugrimstafftheurgist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimstaff Theurgist</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www,kestrelarts.com/images/book.jpg BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 7:05:24 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://dynamic.gamespy.com/~cazic/cazic/ubb/uploads/grimtoo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> First thing you have to remember is that some creatures require you to be at their feet to hit them.  Put your face inside the creature's model and start casting, its the only way to hit some things... my basic rule of thumb is &quot;if I need special spells to hit them I need to be in HTH&quot;<br>
<br>
Regarding resists on Lures, well, there's two ways of looking at this.<br>
<br>
One says that since nobody else can land ANY spells on the Spite Golems, then any success rate is pretty astonishing.<br>
<br>
The other says that Lures have such poor mana/damage ratios and cast so slowly compared to the spells around them that they need to land almost every time to be worth using.  Why?  Because you burn all your mana for nothing and have NO manaless damage to contribute.<br>
<br>
I lean toward the latter but I can sympathise with the first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ulordbug.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordBug</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 7:18:05 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> I haven't fought the new golems yet (that changes tonight), but I didn't have any trouble with the old ones.<br>
<br>
In Hate, Spite Golems have 100% fire, cold, and magic resist.  Poison/Disease works, but not often.  I'd say I get a lure to stick 1/3 to 1/2 on them.  You don't have to be in melee for Spite Golems.  As for second floor.... haven't been up there yet.  I'd guess melee range though for them. <p><BR><BR>
<A HREF="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=15011">Ebdain Ahriman</A> <BR>
53rd Renegade Nuclear Technician<BR>
Carassed by the touch of fire<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usoliceia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soliceia </A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://members.home.net/dnl20/soliceia.GIF BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 9:52:16 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/dnl20/soliceia.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> Well, this is another oppurtunity to remind you that lures do nothing other than make us less efficient casters. Who cares if they hit, they suck up mana and take a long time to cast, therefore reducing our efficiency. Since our class is TOTALLY dependant on mana based damage, we should be efficient. In my honest opinion, if you want a nice fix to our class, make all of our spells lure. Take the whole series out.<br>
<br>
<br>
Soliceia Arcanus---Just waiting for Rombus to shoot this down, CURSE his optimism! <p>Knowledge is power, so to be unknown is to be invunerable.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unucle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nucle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/01 10:21:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lures and resists</span><hr size=1> 25% seems very low...<br>
